fields.name: Project Extent
fields.description: Represents a single node in a graph
fields.instructions: Draw a polygon representing your project's extent. These bounds will serve as the default for the cache seed bounds, search result grid bounds, and map bounds in search, cards, and reports

fields.name: Mapbox API
fields.description: Represents a single node in a graph
fields.instructions: Arches uses the Mapbox mapping library for map display and data creation.  Arches also supports Mapbox basemaps and other services

fields.name: Map Zoom
fields.description: Represents a single node in a graph
fields.instructions: You can define the zoom behavior of your maps by specifying max/min and default values.  Zoom level 0 shows the whole world (and is the minimum zoom level).  Most map services support a maximum of 20 or so zoom levels

fields.description: Initial settings for Arches maps displayed in reports, cards, and search

fields.name: Search Results Grid
fields.description: Represents a single node in a graph
fields.instructions: Arches aggregates search results and displays them as hexagons.  You will need to set default parameters for the hexagon size  and its precision.
